commitResults.messageTitle: Add more OOP : Parser class, Command class , AddCommand class, DeleteCommand class, ExitCommand class, MarkCommand class, UnmarkCommand class, ListCommand class, FindCommand class
Add assertions to all Command's child classes, Storage class and TaskList class.
commitResults.messageBody:
There is no existing assertion.

Assertions are used to define assumptions about the program state so that during the runtime, it can indicates a possible bug in the code.

Let's ,
*add assertions about the isExit boolean value at execute methods in Command's child classes. Doing so will ensure that the respective command's isExit value is correct
*add assertion about the strings that is read from a file at readFile() method in Storage class. Doing so will ensure that the line read is in correct format.
*add assertions about the noOfTasks value at add and delete method in TaskList class. Doing so will ensure that there is no negative noOfTasks.

commitResults.messageTitle: Improve code quality in Command and its child class by removing unused variable
commitResults.messageBody:
*The Command and its child class contain isExit attribute that is not used at all.
*The Command's execute method pass in storage parameter that is not used in the method.

These unused parameter and attribute may cause confusion for the readers.

Let's,
*remove the isExit attributes in Command and all its child classes.
*remove the storage parameter in the execute method in the Command and all its child class.
*update the execute call in the Duke class by passing only task and ui.

commitResults.messageTitle: Improve Code Quality in by avoiding long methods, deep nesting, complicated expressions and code duplication.
commitResults.messageBody:
*Deadline and Event class : toString method contains complicated expressions in the return statement.
*Parser : parse method is long and splitDescriptionAndDate method is deeply nested.
*Storage : readFile method is long.
*TaskList : findTaskWithThisKeyword contains a print line.
*Ui : printList and printMatchingList contains duplicated code.

Avoiding long method, deep nesting, complicated expression and code duplication can improve the readability of the code.

Let's,
*Extract out the time.format() in the return statement in the Deadline and Event's toString method. Evaluate it before the return statement.
*Extract out the code fragment related to addCommand in parse method in Parser class. Turn this code fragment into a new parseAddCommand method.
*Use Guard Clauses in splitDescriptionAndDate method in Parser class.
*Extract out the code fragment that process the String into task in the readFile method in Storage class. Turn this code fragment into a new readTask method.
*Remove the print statement in the findTaskWithThisKeyword method in TaskList class. Put the print statement in printMatchingList method in Ui class.
*Extract out duplicated code in the printList and printMatchingList method in Ui class. Create a new getPrintedList method that contains the duplicated code.

commitResults.messageTitle: Improve Code Quality by structuring code logically.
commitResults.messageBody:
There are no blank lines in between the code.

Adding blank lines in between certain code can improve code's readability.

Let's add blank lines in between codes to group to related statements together.
Use CheckStyle to detect code style violations and correct it accordingly.

The deadlines is not sorted by date.

Adding a SortDeadline command can make the application more user-friendly because users now can call this command to see a list of deadlines that is sorted by dates. The deadline with the earliest deadline will be at the top of the list and the latest deadline will be at the bottom.

Let's,
* Add a TimeComparator class to compare the time.
* Add SortDeadlineCommand class, update Ui and Parser class.
* Add attribute : a list of deadlines in the taskList class and add the respective method to update and get deadlines list.
